027-9af8-f8b1120420ce",536870917]],["^15",[2333,"^3","- Argument\n\t- Deduction\n\t\t- Follows from premises with necessity\n\t- Induction\n\t\t- Follows from premises with probability, because the following is not conclusive\n\t\t\t- Most X have Y\n\t\t\t  This is X\n\t\t\t  Therefore, this X has Y\n\t\t- Is mostly but not necessarily in form of generalization\n\t\t- Limitations\n\t\t\t- Future\n\t\t\t- Intractable past\n\t\t\t- Unobservable nature and universe\n\t\t\t- Extent of human observation: cognition, memory, etc.\n\t- Validity and soundness\n\t\t- Validity is the topic-neutral property of argument's structure. Basically \"if the premise is true\", the conclusion of which can be:\n\t\t\t- Probable\n\t\t\t  collapsed:: true\n\t\t\t\t- If I get flush on river, I probably will win.\n\t\t\t\t  I got flush.\n\t\t\t\t  I probably won\n\t\t\t- Certain\n\t\t\t  collapsed:: true\n\t\t\t\t- If the lines are parallel, they don't intersect.\n\t\t\t\t- The lines are parallel.\n\t\t\t\t- They don't intersect.\n\t\t- If the premise of a valid argument is actually true it's sound.\n\t- Refutations of an argument\n\t\t- The argument is invalid\n\t\t- One or more of the premises are false\n\t\t- The conclusion is false as in *reductio ad absurdum*\n\t\t\t- Just shows that the conclusion must be false but doesn't refute the argument itself, because it doesn't indicate *what* is wrong with the argument, only that *something* must be wrong with it.\n\t- Abduction or inference to the best explanation\n\t  collapsed:: true\n\t\t- Similarity to Induction\n\t\t\t- Doesn't necessarily follow from the premises like deduction does\n\t\t- Difference from Induction\n\t\t\t- Appeals implicitly or explicitly to additional reasoning whereas induction *only* appeals to frequency or statistics\n\t- Hypothetico‐deductive method\n\t\t- Start with a hypothesis\n\t\t  logseq.order-list-type:: number\n\t\t- Deduce which facts follow\n\t\t  logseq.order-list-type:: number\n\t\t- Make an experiment to test them\n\t\t  logseq.order-list-type:: number\n\t\t- Make a deduction whether the hypothesis is true or false\n\t\t  logseq.order-list-type:: number\n\t-\n- Paragraph markers\n  id:: 65677c5b-9d97-4bc0-b2b7-75c75bd7dca6\n\t- Explication\n\t\t- XPL\n\t- In other words\n\t\t- IE\n\t- Example\n\t\t- EG\n\t- My commentary\n\t\t- Commetary",536870917]],["^15",[2333,"^16",1772635622900,536870917]],["^15",[2333,"^Z","pages/Philosopher's Toolkit.md",536870917]],["^15",[2334,"^K",1772635622900,536870917]],["^15",[2334,"^[",2333,536870917]],["^15",[2334,"^@",false,536870917]],["^15",[2334,"^Y","philosopher's toolkit",536870917]],["^15",[2334,"^11","Philosopher's Toolkit",536870917]],["^15",[2334,"^B",1772635622900,536870917]],["^15",[2334,"^;","~u69a845e6-abbd-4ef2-8543-9bb183a93f7f",536870917]],["^15",[2335,"^Q","They don't intersect.",536870917]],["^15",[2335,"^O","^17",536870917]],["^15",[2335,"^F",2358,536870917]],["^15",[2335,"^X",2334,536870917]],["^15",[2335,"^V",2373,536870917]],["^15",[2335,"^U",2334,536870917]],["^15",[2335,"^;","~u69a845e6-1634-4836-a924-18f8d262a185",536870917]],["^15",[2336,"^Q","Follows from premises with probability, because the following is not conclusive",536870917]],["^15",[2336,"^O","^17",536870917]],["^15",[2336,"^F",2354,536870917]],["^15",[2336,"^X",2334,536870917]],["^15",[2336,"^V",2354,536870917]],["^15",[2336,"^U",2334,536870917]],["^15",[2336,"^;","~u69a845e6-1058-4741-8de2-d7da73a9ebe4",536870917]],["^15",[2337,"^Q","Validity is the topic-neutral property of argument's structure. Basically \"if the premise is true\", the conclusion of which can be:",536870917]],["^15",[2337,"^O","^17",536870917]],["^15",[2337,"^F",2379,536870917]],["^15",[2337,"^X",2334,536870917]],["^15",[2337,"^V",2379,536870917]],["^15",[2337,"^U",2334,536870917]],["^15",[2337,"^;","~u69a845e6-2f22-4afe-9dcf-d4d5eb1aa79e",536870917]],["^15",[2338,"^Q","Hypothetico‐deductive method",536870917]],["^15",[2338,"^O","^17",536870917]],["^15",[2338,"^F",2370,536