skell_(Graham_Hutton_[Hutton,_Graham])_(Z-Library)_1716905671265_0.pdf](../assets/Programming_in_Haskell_(Graham_Hutton_[Hutton,_Graham])_(Z-Library)_1716905671265_0.pdf)\nfile-path:: ../assets/Programming_in_Haskell_(Graham_Hutton_[Hutton,_Graham])_(Z-Library)_1716905671265_0.pdf\n\n- a function is a mapping that takes one or more arguments and produces a single result, and is deﬁned using an equation that gives a name for the function, a name for each of its arguments, and a body that speciﬁes how the result can be calculated in terms of the arguments.\n  ls-type:: annotation\n  hl-page:: 21\n  hl-color:: yellow\n  id:: 6655e7dd-1d90-466f-ae25-bb9dafe7530b\n- functional programming can be viewed as a style of programming in which the basic method of computation is the application of functions to arguments. In turn, a functional programming language is one that supports and encourages the functional style.\n  ls-type:: annotation\n  hl-page:: 22\n  hl-color:: yellow\n  id:: 6655e8e5-a7d4-453e-ba79-e776cc010ba9",536870917]],["^15",[3021,"^16",1772635623372,536870917]],["^15",[3021,"^Z","pages/hls__Programming_in_Haskell_(Graham_Hutton_[Hutton,_Graham])_(Z-Library)_1716905671265_0.md",536870917]],["^15",[3022,"^K",1772635623371,536870917]],["^15",[3022,"^[",3021,536870917]],["^15",[3022,"^@",false,536870917]],["^15",[3022,"^Y","hls__programming_in_haskell_(graham_hutton_[hutton,_graham])_(z-library)_1716905671265_0",536870917]],["^15",[3022,"^11","hls__Programming_in_Haskell_(Graham_Hutton_[Hutton,_Graham])_(Z-Library)_1716905671265_0",536870917]],["^15",[3022,"^?",["^ ","~:file","[Programming_in_Haskell_(Graham_Hutton_[Hutton,_Graham])_(Z-Library)_1716905671265_0.pdf](../assets/Programming_in_Haskell_(Graham_Hutton_[Hutton,_Graham])_(Z-Library)_1716905671265_0.pdf)","~:file-path","../assets/Programming_in_Haskell_(Graham_Hutton_[Hutton,_Graham])_(Z-Library)_1716905671265_0.pdf"],536870917]],["^15",[3022,"^4",["^ ","^26","[Programming_in_Haskell_(Graham_Hutton_[Hutto